  <div class="about__body">
    <p>
      For more than ten years, I've had the honor of standing beside couples on the most
      meaningful day of their lives. Across 230+ weddings, I've learned that the best days
      aren't the ones with the biggest budgets or the trendiest details — they're the ones
      where the couple felt fully present, completely cared for, and free to simply be in love.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's the experience I plan toward. I'm not here to impose a template or hand you a
      checklist and disappear. I'm here as your partner: listening closely to your vision,
      anticipating the details you haven't thought of yet, and quietly handling the hundred
      small things on the day so you never have to.
    </p>
    <p>
      I work with couples, families, and clients of all backgrounds, identities, and love
      stories — always with respect, warmth, and a genuine investment in your happiness.
      Many of my couples tell me that by the end of the process, I felt less like a vendor
      and more like family. That's exactly how I hope you'll feel too.
    </p>
    <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--dark">Let's Talk</a>
  </div>
</section>

